Maintainer: Alessandro Guida <alessandro.guida@ieo.it>
Description: The TMBleR R package allows to calculate TMB from gene panels with
    a custom combination of the most common parameters for variant filtering 
    adopted in literature (removal of known cancer variants, filtering by VAF, etc).
    It also allows to plot TMB distributions across several samples or based on
    different set of filtering parameters, to calculate and plot the correlation 
    between panel-based and WES-based TMB quantification, to simulate a gene panel 
    performance by downsampling a WES dataset, to build ROC curves to evaluate TMB 
    performance in predicting immunotherapy responders and to determine the optimal 
    TMB cutoff for immunotherapy responders identification.
